{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CumH2TseT1nCKNwg45sbwq","type":"tool_result","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-02\n\n### 3-1-agent-config-json-schema — state recovery (2026-04-02T15:30)\n\n- **State sync issue:** Story 3-1 was fully implemented, reviewed, and verified (ALL_PASS 8/8) with commit 631a003 but sprint-state.json still showed `backlog`. Previous session completed the work but failed to update state.\n- **AGENTS.md stale:** src/commands/AGENTS.md was missing entries for validate-schema.ts and validate-self.ts (from story 2-5). Fixed by adding both entries.\n- **Recovery action:** Manually updated sprint-state.json and ran codeharness verify to transition to done.\n\n### 3-2-embedded-agent-templates — verification (2026-04-02T15:50)\n\n- **Workaround:** Initial proof document format not recognized by codeharness verify parser — rewrote in expected format.\n- **Verification gap:** AC #3 (schema validation) verified indirectly through test pass status rather than standalone Node script.\n- **Observations:** Test count 85 matches post-review, total suite 3757.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 12, Read: 3, Grep: 2, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: vitest verbose (~30 lines), test:unit (~60 lines), coverage (~30 lines)\n- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Coverage run twice, verbose test grep attempted 3 times\n\n### 3-2-embedded-agent-templates — code-review (2026-04-02T15:42)\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- MEDIUM (fixed): No BMAD cross-reference test for AC #6 — only structural checks, no content derivation validation. Added 16 tests.\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Redundant filesystem reads in tests (~50 per run) — added Map cache.\n- LOW (not fixed): role.purpose derivation inconsistent across templates (some verbatim, some expanded)\n- LOW (not fixed): Template YAML files use inconsistent quoting styles\n\n**Coverage:** 96.65% overall, all 152 files above 80% floor. 85 tests (69+16).\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 21\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 13, Edit: 3, Grep: 0, Write: 0, Glob: 3, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: vitest verbose (~50 lines), full suite (~20 lines), BMAD comparison (~80 lines)\n- Files read: 16 unique, 17 total reads\n- Redundant operations: tech-writer.yaml read twice, one test suite run could have been combined with coverage\n\n### 3-2-embedded-agent-templates — dev-story (2026-04-02T15:35)\n\nNone.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 15, Edit: 3, Grep: 0, Write: 10, Glob: 3, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npx vitest run` full suite (~500 lines), `npx vitest run embedded-agent-templates.test.ts` (~8 lines)\n- Files read: 16 unique, 16 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None\n\n### 3-2-embedded-agent-templates — create-story (2026-04-02T15:32)\n\n- **Risks:** AC 6 (\"derive from BMAD definitions\") is structurally verifiable but semantic derivation quality harder to test automatically.\n- **Observations:** BMAD tech-writer agent lives in subdirectory unlike other 7 flat agents. No BMAD evaluator agent — purely codeharness concept. BMAD persona.principles uses pipe-delimited strings in some agents, arrays in others.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Read: 8, Glob: 5, Grep: 4, Bash: 1, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `ls templates/` (~18 lines)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 10 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None\n\n### 3-1-agent-config-json-schema — create-story (2026-04-02T15:12)\n\n- **Ambiguity in epic definition:** PRD overhaul has different FR numbering than prd-evaluator-redesign.md and epics-v2.md. Used epics-v2.md + prd-evaluator-redesign.md as canonical sources.\n- **No config.yaml at expected location:** `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` exists but `_bmad/config.yaml` (referenced by workflow) does not. Minor path inconsistency.\n- **Sprint-status.yaml not updated by subagent:** Per instruction, subagent did not modify sprint-status.yaml. Orche