{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VeFEEU42rsH7U5pSspj5f8","type":"tool_result","content":"158-\n159-```yaml\n160-# .codeharness/workflows/default.patch.yaml\n161:extends: embedded://default\n162-overrides:\n163-  tasks:\n164-    implement:\n--\n178-\n179-```yaml\n180-# .codeharness/agents/dev.patch.yaml\n181:extends: embedded://dev\n182-overrides:\n183-  personality:\n184-    traits:\n185-      rigor: 0.9\n186:prompt_patches:\n187-  append: |\n188-    This project uses React + Vite. Run npm run build before\n189-    considering implementation complete.\n--\n299-.codeharness/workflows/     # project workflow patches or custom workflows\n300-```\n301-\n302:Resolution: embedded → user patch → project patch (sequential merge). Patches use `extends: embedded://name` with structured `overrides:` and freeform `prompt_patches:`.\n303-\n304-### Installation & Setup\n305-\n--\n336-### Agent Configuration\n337-\n338-- FR7: System ships 9 embedded agents: dev, qa, architect, pm, sm, analyst, ux-designer, tech-writer, evaluator\n339:- FR8: User can create custom agents at project level (`.codeharness/agents/`) or user level (`~/.codeharness/agents/`)\n340:- FR9: User can patch embedded or user-level agents via `extends:` with structured `overrides:` and freeform `prompt_patches:`\n341:- FR10: Agent config supports BMAD-compatible base fields (name, role, persona with identity/communication_style/principles) and optional PersonaNexus-compatible traits (10 dimensions, 0-1 scale)\n342:- FR11: System resolves agent config through embedded → user → project patch chain at runtime\n343:- FR12: System compiles resolved agent config into Claude Code inline subagent definition for SDK dispatch\n344-\n345-### Workflow Configuration\n346-\n347-- FR13: User can create custom workflows at project level (`.codeharness/workflows/`) or user level (`~/.codeharness/workflows/`)\n348:- FR14: User can patch embedded or user-level workflows via `extends:` with structured `overrides:`\n349:- FR15: System resolves workflow config through embedded → user → project patch chain at runtime\n350-\n351-### Workflow Execution\n352-\n--\n420-\n421-- NFR6: Engine state survives process crashes — on restart, execution resumes from the last completed task\n422-- NFR7: Evaluator session timeout does not crash the engine — timeout is a scored failure, not a fatal error\n423:- NFR8: All engine state is persisted to disk after each task completion\n424:- NFR9: Engine handles programmatic agent dispatch API errors gracefully (API limits, network failures) with specific error reporting\n425:- NFR10: Long-running executions (4+ hours) do not degrade in correctness or accumulate resource leaks\n426-\n427-### Integration\n428-\n429:- NFR11: Engine uses the official programmatic agent dispatch API — no direct CLI process spawning\n430:- NFR12: BMAD agent configs are read-only — engine never modifies agent YAML files\n431-- NFR13: Docker container lifecycle (start, exec, stop) is managed by the engine, not delegated to agents\n432-- NFR14: Observability stack is optional — engine runs without it, evaluator reports reduced capability\n433-"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0155ShxPeo4aZZxJMe6PsZMC","session_id":"82c789c3-0c3c-4e9f-a910-db433860b9ed","uuid":"3910492c-d64f-4ade-8801-cd099d45f1bc","timestamp":"2026-04-02T15:54:07.385Z"}
