{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0155ShxPeo4aZZxJMe6PsZMC","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**Story Details:**\n- Story ID: 3.3\n- Story Key: 3-3-agent-resolver-module\n- File: `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/3-3-agent-resolver-module.md`\n- Status: ready-for-dev\n- Sprint-status.yaml: NOT modified (per user instruction)\n\n**Story covers FR7-FR12:**\n- Embedded agent loading from `templates/agents/`\n- 3-layer patch chain: embedded -> user (`~/.codeharness/agents/`) -> project (`.codeharness/agents/`)\n- Deep merge with objects-recursive / arrays-replace / scalars-replace strategy\n- `compileSubagentDefinition()` producing SDK-ready plain object\n- `AgentResolveError` for malformed patches, silent skip for missing patches\n- 10 ACs, all tagged `test-provable` (no running app needed -- pure file I/O and object transformation)\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Problems encountered:**\n- The workflow references `workflow.md` but the actual file is `workflow.yaml` + `instructions.xml`. Used both to reconstruct full instructions.\n\n**Workarounds applied:**\n- None significant. The `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` is not yet a dependency, so `SubagentDefinition` is defined as a plain TypeScript interface in this module. Story 4-1 will add the actual SDK dependency. This is noted in the dev notes.\n\n**Risks identified:**\n- AC #9 (<200ms for all 9 agents) depends on filesystem speed and may be flaky on slow CI runners. The test should use a generous threshold or `performance.now()` with margin.\n- The `extends: user://name` pattern (project patch extending a user-level agent) is explicitly deferred. If a future story needs it, the resolver will need extension.\n- Deep merge \"arrays replace\" strategy is a design choice not explicitly confirmed in the architecture doc -- it's inferred from the PRD examples where `flow.replace` is shown. If the intent was array concatenation for principles, this would be a behavioral mismatch.\n\n**Observations:**\n- All 10 ACs are `test-provable` -- this module is pure data transformation with no runtime dependencies, making it one of the cleanest modules to test.\n- The `compileSubagentDefinition()` function deliberately uses a plain interface rather than importing SDK types, keeping the dependency boundary clean for story 4-1.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 19\n- By tool: Bash: 4, Read: 12, Grep: 3, Glob: 6, Write: 1, Edit: 0, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `git diff --stat` (~17 lines), `git log --oneline` (~10 lines), `ls templates/agents/` (~9 lines)\n- Files read: 13 unique, 13 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: None. Each file was read once. The sprint-status.yaml was read once during initial discovery."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a76d8ef0204a6b144 (use SendMessage with to: 'a76d8ef0204a6b144' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 82107\ntool_uses: 39\nduration_ms: 234324</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"82c789c3-0c3c-4e9f-a910-db433860b9ed","uuid":"28afeae7-4534-43da-bd6e-93a68e7df413","timestamp":"2026-04-02T15:56:33.954Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-create-story for story 3-3-agent-resolver-module. The sprint-status.yaml is at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml. Auto-discover the next backlog story and create it. For each AC, append a verification tier tag using this decision tree:\n\n**Tier Decision Tree (append one `<!-- verification: tier -->` tag per AC):**\n- `test-provable` — AC can be verified by building the project and running tests/linters/grep. No running app needed.\n- `runtime-provable` — AC requires running the app locally and checking its behavior (CLI output, HTTP response, process lifecycle).\n- `environment-provable` — AC requires a full environment (Docker stack, database, observability, multi-service interaction).